theorem
Th10: (y in ( Union f ) iff (ex x st (x in ( dom f ) & y in ( f . x ))))
proof
thus (y in ( Union f ) implies (ex x st (x in ( dom f ) & y in ( f . x ))))
proof
assume y in ( Union f );
then consider X such that A1: y in X and A2: X in ( rng f ) by TARSKI:def 4;
consider x such that A3: (x in ( dom f ) & X = ( f . x )) by A2,FUNCT_1:def 3;
take x;
thus thesis by A1,A3;
end;

given x such that
A4: x in ( dom f )
and
A5: y in ( f . x );

( f . x ) in ( rng f ) by A4,FUNCT_1:def 3;
hence thesis by A5,TARSKI:def 4;
end;
